Come, almighty to deliver, Let us all thy life receive Fix in us thy humble dwelling, All thy faithful mercies crown. Suddenly return, and never, Nevermore thy temples leave: 8 Jesus, thou art all compassion, Pure, unbounded love thou art: ; Thee we would be always blessing, Serve thee as thy hosts above, Visit us with thy salvation, Enter every trembling heart.
